  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Integration Specialist",
  "description": "<p>Join the fintech revolution with Mambu, the leading SaaS cloud banking platform. We're on a mission to make banking better for a billion people. Explore exciting career opportunities and help shape the future of financial services. Learn more <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/mambu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here</a><u></u></p><p>As a Senior Integration Consultant, you lead the design and delivery of cloud-native, scalable integration architectures that power modern digital banking. You act as the primary technical leader for customers, guiding them through solution design, orchestrating complex ecosystems, and ensuring successful adoption of Mambu’s composable banking platform.</p><p><strong>What You Will Do:</strong></p><p>●     <strong>Lead customer engagements</strong> across implementation and\npost–go-live, acting as the main technical point of contact.</p><p>●     <strong>Drive architecture and design</strong>, covering REST APIs, events, webhooks, batch and real-time integrations, and end-to-end system flows.</p><p>●     <strong>Conduct workshops and discovery sessions</strong>, aligning stakeholders on data flows, constraints, and solution outcomes.</p><p>●     <strong>Collaborate cross-functionally</strong> with Sales, Product, Engineering, Solutions Architects, and Customer Success on design decisions and pre-sales scoping.</p><p>●     <strong>Ensure performance, resilience, and reliability</strong>, modelling throughput, designing for peak loads and implementing HA/FT patterns.</p><p>●     <strong>Guide customers on best practices</strong>, including error handling, asynchronous processing, event-driven patterns, and secure networking.</p><p><strong>What You Will Bring:</strong></p><p>●     Strong experience with <strong>cloud-native integration architecture</strong> across AWS, Azure, or GCP.</p><p>●    Strong system design skills in <strong>scalability, distributed\ntransactions, consistency models, and latency-aware patterns</strong>.</p><p>●    At least one <strong>cloud architect–level certification </strong>(AWS/Azure/GCP).</p><p>●     Deep understanding of <strong>REST APIs, event-driven systems, webhooks, messaging queues, microservices, and\nserverless patterns</strong>.</p><p>●     Solid grounding in <strong>VPC and hybrid networking</strong>, private connectivity, secure routing, and cloud\nnetworking fundamentals.</p><p>●     Ability to design <strong>resilient, fault-tolerant integration flows</strong> that withstand partial failures and degraded dependencies.</p><p>●     <strong>Excellent communication, documentation, and stakeholder leadership</strong>, with the ability to engage both executives and engineers.</p><p>●     <strong>Financial services domain knowledge </strong>(fintech, core banking, lending, or payments) is strongly valued.</p>",
